27/07/2007
ROME, Italy -- Turkey, Italy, and Greece signed an agreement in Rome on Thursday (July 26th) on the construction of a pipeline to transport natural gas from the Caspian basin to Europe.
According to the agreement, the natural gas pipeline linking Turkey with Greece will be extended to Italy.
The construction works are due to begin next year, and to be completed by end of 2011.
(Hurriyet, Zaman, Radikal - 27/07/07;
NTV, ANA-MPA, AFP - 26/07/07)
